-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                             Output Supply ResponseOn Malawi Maize Production (1991 - 2025): An ARDL Approach
                                                                              Joe Wasonga Ochieng'
                                                                              1 Jul 2026, 15:02:48
A time-series analysis framework designed to estimate the output supply response of Maize in Malawi. The analysis employs an Autoregressive Distributed Lag (ARDL) bounds testing 
approach to evaluate both short-run dynamic impacts and long-run cointegrated relationships between production output and key economic/climatic determinants.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Time-Series Definition: Declares the dataset as time-series format using tsset year.

 tsset year

Time variable: year, 1991 to 2025
        Delta: 1 unit

2. Log-Transformations: Converts raw metrics into log-form for elasticity modeling

. gen lnoutput     = ln(output)

. gen lnarea       = ln(area)

. gen lnprice      = ln(price)

. gen lnfertilizer = ln(fertilizer)

. gen lnrainfall   = ln(rainfall)

. gen lncpi        = ln(cpi)


3. Baseline Estimation: An initial Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) multi-variable regression to establish raw correlations.

